external_knowledge:
Electrical Engineering students are those listed under the 'Electrical Engineering' department in the database;
Active courses mean the status is 'active' in the course enrollments;
A student is awaiting grades if their grades are listed as NULL in the grades table.

- 'Smith' in the instructor's name indicates filtering instructors who have 'Smith' as part of their name; 
- The grades 'A', 'B', and 'C' refer to the top three grading categories; 
- 'Distinct files submitted' means the count of unique submission files related to the grades.

Top-performing students are those who have received an 'A' grade; Active means their course enrollment status is 'active'.;
Excelling is defined by getting an 'A' grade in assessments.;
Assessments are part of the course curriculum and are evaluated to measure student performance.;

sql:
SELECT students.student_name, students.major, grades.grade
FROM students
INNER JOIN grades ON students.student_id = grades.student_id;

SELECT student_id, student_name, gpa, RANK() OVER(ORDER BY gpa DESC) as ranking 
FROM students
WHERE department = 'Electrical Engineering' AND year_of_study = 2;
